---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Workflow Examples | BeaconGuard Regulated AI Operations"
  description="Explore BeaconGuard workflow examples for healthcare AI operations review, financial crime and fraud review, and regulated internal automation."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Workflow Examples</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard is engineered for high-risk, human-reviewed workflows where AI output or automation may assist a regulated decision path, while policy control remains deterministic and reviewable.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Healthcare AI Operations Review</h2>
    <p>
      A hospital operations team requests AI assistance for a workflow involving sensitive operational or patient-related context.
      BeaconGuard evaluates the request before model execution, checks policy for data sensitivity and user role, and returns allow, deny, or needs-review.
      Evidence is preserved for privacy, compliance, and audit review.
    </p>
    <h3>Example controls</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Detects potential PHI context</li>
      <li>Requires approved AI pathway</li>
      <li>Routes sensitive requests for privacy or compliance review</li>
      <li>Blocks unapproved model endpoints</li>
      <li>Preserves decision evidence</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted-copy">
      This example uses patient-related context and PHI-sensitive workflows carefully. It does not claim diagnosis, treatment recommendation, direct clinical decision support, hospital deployment, or HIPAA compliance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Financial Crime / Fraud Review</h2>
    <p>
      In this workflow, AI can assist analysis for cross-border AML, KYC, fraud, or financial dispute review, but no model inference proceeds without BeaconGuard policy evaluation and preserved decision evidence.
      Financial services remains an example use case, not the whole product identity.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Application Input:</strong> The financial or analyst application submits a cross-border case for AI-assisted summarization or recommendation.</li>
      <li><strong>Gateway Intake:</strong> BeaconGuard intercepts the payload.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Trust &amp; Replay Validation:</strong> The payload is cryptographically validated and checked for replay.
        <strong>Deny path is executed if invalid.</strong>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Deterministic Policy Evaluation:</strong> The request is checked against governed policy constraints for required AML, KYC, or workflow evidence.
        <strong>Deny path is executed if incomplete or out of bounds.</strong>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Control Outcome:</strong> BeaconGuard returns allow, deny, or needs-review after deterministic policy enforcement.</li>
      <li><strong>Decision Evidence:</strong> A structured JSON decision record is retained for architecture review and security inspection.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Regulated Internal Automation Review</h2>
    <p>
      An internal automation or AI agent attempts to perform an action against a regulated system. BeaconGuard checks policy before execution, blocks unauthorized actions, and records evidence for operational review.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Checks user, role, workflow, environment, requested action, and change window</li>
      <li>Blocks automation outside approved role or operating conditions</li>
      <li>Routes higher-risk actions for human approval</li>
      <li>Preserves decision evidence for security, risk, operations, and audit review</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Architecture View</h2>
    <div class="workflow-diagram">
      <img src="/Workflow.png" alt="BeaconGuard control boundary workflow diagram" />
      <p class="workflow-diagram-caption">
        High level component boundaries and trust domains in the control architecture.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Decision Evidence</h2>
    <p>
      Each workflow emits structured enforcement records only after BeaconGuard has decided allow, deny, or needs-review. Reviewers inspect the decision signal,
      enforcement fields, trust validation, and evidence hashes to determine exactly what control path executed.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/proof-evidence">Review Decision Evidence</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/security">Security</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/reviewer-kit">Reviewer Kit</a>
    </div>
  </section>

<style>
  .workflow-diagram {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }

  .workflow-diagram img {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 720px;
    height: auto;
  }

  .workflow-diagram-caption {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    width: 100%;
  }
</style>
</BaseLayout>

